            {
              "id": "db978cde-0205-3536-b72b-abc6f6250d0f",
              "name": "Potential Nil Dereference Vulnerability in `vcnResponse` Variable Modification",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided has a potential nil dereference vulnerability. This occurs when the `vcnResponse` variable is nil and the program tries to access its `RawResponse` field. If `vcnResponse` is nil, this will result in a runtime panic, causing the program to crash.\n\nThis vulnerability is a common mistake in Go programming language, where the error returned by a function is not nil, but the other returned values are not checked for nil before being used.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always check if the returned value is not nil before trying to access its fields or methods. This is a good practice in Go programming language to avoid runtime panics.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\nvcnResponse, err := virtualNetworkClient.ListVcns(context.Background(), vcnRequest)\nif err != nil {\n\thttpErr := httperror.ErrorCode{}\n\tif vcnResponse != nil && vcnResponse.RawResponse != nil {\n\t\thttpErr.Status = vcnResponse.RawResponse.StatusCode\n\t} else {\n\t\thttpErr.Status = httperror.ServerError.Status\n\t}\n\tlogrus.Debugf(\"[oci-handler] error listing VCNs with Virtual Network client: %v\", err)\n\treturn nil, httpErr.Status, err\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we added an additional check `vcnResponse != nil` before trying to access `vcnResponse.RawResponse`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `context` standard library for managing the context of the request.\n- `logrus` for logging debug information.\n- `httperror` for handling HTTP errors.\n- `virtualNetworkClient` for interacting with the virtual network client.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
