            {
              "id": "2811b326-154d-33a3-a2ee-ea62e9ee36a0",
              "name": "Unsecured Session Cookie Detected",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Unsecured Session Cookie Detected\" is a vulnerability that occurs when a web application does not properly secure its session cookies. This can lead to potential attacks such as session hijacking, where an attacker can steal the session cookie and impersonate the user.\n\nIn the Go programming language, this vulnerability can occur when the `Secure` attribute of the `http.Cookie` struct is set to `false` or not set at all. The `Secure` attribute ensures that the cookie is only sent over HTTPS, preventing it from being intercepted by an attacker.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, always set the `Secure` attribute of the `http.Cookie` struct to `true`. This ensures that the cookie is only sent over secure connections. Additionally, consider setting the `HttpOnly` attribute to `true` to prevent the cookie from being accessed through client-side scripts, further reducing the risk of attacks such as cross-site scripting (XSS).\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the fixed version of the provided code:\n\n```go\npkceCookie := &http.Cookie{\n\tName:     pkceVerifierCookieName,\n\tValue:    value,\n\tSecure:   true, // Always set Secure to true\n\tPath:     \"/\",\n\tHttpOnly: true,\n\tExpires:  time.Now().Add(time.Minute * 10),\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `net/http`: for the `http.Cookie` struct.\n- `time`: for the `time.Now` function and `time.Minute` constant.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP - SecureFlag](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Session_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html#secure-attribute)\n- [OWASP - HttpOnly](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Session_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html#httponly-attribute)\n- [CWE-614: Sensitive Cookie in HTTPS Session Without 'Secure' Attribute](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/614.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-614",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/614.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-614"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "8e56bc40-d3b9-3bde-9655-7d4392762335",
              "name": "Unsecured Session Cookie Detected",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Unsecured Session Cookie Detected\" is a vulnerability that occurs when a web application does not properly secure its session cookies. This can lead to potential attacks such as session hijacking, where an attacker can steal a user's session cookie and impersonate them.\n\nIn the provided Go code, the `Secure` attribute of the `http.Cookie` struct is set to `isSecure`, which may not always be `true`. If `isSecure` is `false`, the cookie will be transmitted over unsecured HTTP connections, making it vulnerable to interception and theft.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, always set the `Secure` attribute of the `http.Cookie` struct to `true`. This ensures that the cookie is only transmitted over secure HTTPS connections. Additionally, consider setting the `HttpOnly` attribute to `true` to prevent the cookie from being accessed through client-side scripts, further reducing the risk of theft.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```go\npkceCookie := &http.Cookie{\n\tName:     pkceVerifierCookieName,\n\tValue:    \"\",\n\tSecure:   true,\n\tHttpOnly: true,\n\tExpires:  time.Now().Add(time.Second * -10),\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `net/http`: for the `http.Cookie` struct.\n- `time`: for the `time.Now` function and `time.Second` constant.\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-614: Sensitive Cookie in HTTPS Session Without 'Secure' Attribute](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/614.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-614",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/614.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-614"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "6d3e8459-9016-378b-ae34-db3dd8a427b3",
              "name": "Potential Nil Dereference Vulnerability in `group` Variable Modification",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a potential nil dereference vulnerability in the `group` variable modification. This vulnerability occurs when the `group` variable is `nil` and the program tries to access its `Name` property. If `group` is `nil`, the program will panic and crash, leading to a denial of service.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always check if a variable is `nil` before trying to access its properties or methods. This can be done by adding an additional condition in the `if` statement to check if `group` is `nil`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the code:\n\n```go\ngroup, err = s.groups.Update(group)\nif err != nil || group == nil {\n    if group == nil {\n        logrus.Error(\"scim::PatchGroup: group is nil\")\n    } else {\n        logrus.Errorf(\"scim::PatchGroup: failed to update group: %s\", err)\n    }\n    writeError(w, NewInternalError())\n    return\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, we added a check for `group == nil` in the `if` statement. If `group` is `nil`, we log an error message and return.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- The `logrus` package for logging errors.\n- The `s.groups.Update` method, which is likely part of a custom package.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-476",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-476"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "3725eb83-0220-3349-bc38-83834a776ced",
              "name": "Potential Nil Dereference Vulnerability due to Modification of `user` Variable",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to a potential nil dereference vulnerability due to the modification of the `user` variable. This vulnerability occurs when the program attempts to access or modify a member of a structure through a null pointer. In this case, if the `user` object is null, the program will crash when trying to access `user.Name`.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to always check if an object is null before trying to access or modify its members. This can be done by adding a null check condition before accessing the `user.Name`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code snippet:\n\n```go\nuser, err = l.users.Get(user.Name, metav1.GetOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) { // The user is no longer, move on.\n        return nil\n    }\n    if user != nil {\n        logrus.Errorf(\"userretention: labeler: error getting user %s: %v\", user.Name, err)\n    } else {\n        logrus.Errorf(\"userretention: labeler: error getting user: %v\", err)\n    }\n    return err\n}\n```\n\nIn the above code, we added a null check for `user` before trying to access `user.Name`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus`\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1`\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-476: NULL Pointer Dereference](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-476",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html"
