            {
              "id": "8db8c765-c7b3-3257-b3ee-f4c3e3cfe269",
              "name": "Vulnerability in ReverseProxy: Misuse of Director over Rewrite for Header Removal",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe vulnerability \"Misuse of Director over Rewrite for Header Removal\" in Go's ReverseProxy is a security issue where the `Director` function is misused, leading to potential security risks. The `Director` function is a part of Go's `http.ReverseProxy` and is used to modify the incoming request's URL, headers, or other properties. If not used correctly, it can lead to security vulnerabilities such as information leakage, unauthorized access, or other potential attacks.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the `Director` function is used to proxy the request without removing or modifying any headers. This can lead to potential security issues if the headers contain sensitive information.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to properly handle headers in the `Director` function. Sensitive headers should be removed or modified before the request is proxied. This can prevent potential information leakage or unauthorized access.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code snippet:\n\n```go\nDirector: func(req *http.Request) {\n    // Remove sensitive headers\n    req.Header.Del(\"Sensitive-Header\")\n\n    if err := p.proxy(req); err != nil {\n        logrus.Infof(\"Failed to proxy: %v\", err)\n    }\n},\n```\n\nIn this fix, the `Sensitive-Header` is removed before the request is proxied.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `net/http`: This is a standard library in Go for HTTP client and server implementations.\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus`: This is a structured logger for Go.\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-346: Origin Validation Error](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/346.html)\n\nPlease note that the links are valid and active for anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-346",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/346.html"
                  }
                ],
                "severity": "MEDIUM",
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "tags": [
